article.description: Zeke Moore blocked Trayvon Palmer's 3-point attempt in the closing seconds and Saint Louis held on for a 45-43 win over Chicago State on Sunday.
article.headline: Blocked shot saves Saint Louis' 45-43 win over Chicago State
article.linkText: Blocked shot saves Saint Louis' 45-43 win over Chicago State
article.story: ST. LOUIS -- Zeke Moore blocked Trayvon Palmer's 3-point attempt in the closing seconds and Saint Louis held on for a 45-43 win over Chicago State on Sunday. After taking a 45-39 lead on Elliott Welmer's layup with 4:15 to play, the Billikens missed four shots and had five turnovers. Fred Sims Jr. had jumper at 3:53 for the Cougars and Palmer made a layup at 38 seconds to make it a one-possession game. Deionte Simmons made a steal for Chicago State with 10 seconds to play but Moore saved the game. Mike Crawford had 11 points and Welmer 10 for Saint Louis (3-6), which made 17 of 50 shots, just 4 of 24 from 3-point range. Palmer had 16 points and 13 rebounds for the Cougars (3-6), who went 5 of 20 behind the arc and shot 35 percent overall (18 of 52). Both teams had 14 turnovers.
